/-!
# AlphaNonNull.Core.SemanticSterility

**Paper 68: SemanticallySterile — incapable of underwriting presence.**

SemanticallySterile(α) means α is incapable of underwriting presence,
manifestation, or semantic actuality. This is semantic/presentational, not
merely causal. A sterile ground could not support qualia, awareness, or
lived semantic content.

Theorem 68.3: (∃x. AlphaManifestation(x)) ⇒ ¬SemanticallySterile(α).
If manifestation exists, α is not sterile.
-/

set_option autoImplicit false

universe v

variable {Ground : Type v}

namespace AlphaNonNull

/--
**SemanticallySterile (α)** — Ground α is incapable of underwriting presence,
manifestation, or semantic actuality.

Semantic/presentational sterility: α could not support qualia, awareness,
or lived semantic content. Distinct from Null (sheer absence) and Inert
(passive backdrop). A sterile ground would be structurally incapable of
the kind of presence that manifestation requires.

**Definition:** See `AlphaNonNull.Bridge.ToGroundManifestation` for the
manifestation-based definition when GroundManifestation context is available.
